  "description": "Query-side selective verifier/repair ablation on top of v29. Keep v29 build memory, retrieval, compiler, temporal event contract, and draft answer prompt unchanged, then run a second clean LLM read only when runtime artifacts indicate risk: uncertainty/missing evidence, short collection answer, or temporal answer/evidence conflict. The repair prompt uses only question text, route, retrieved Memory Context, draft answer, and draft JSON; it does not use gold, judge output, benchmark labels, category, sample ids, qids, row indices, test feedback, or sample-level rules. This borrows verifier/reflection discipline from creating001 evidence tables, SimpleMem reflection retrieval, DeepResearch reflect loops, Memento failure-aware reflection, and method.md's retrieve+evidence table+verifier direction, while keeping the trigger general and token-budgeted.",
